              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "loans", "{{loan_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Loan detail + status timeline."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/loans/:id/cancel",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/loans/{{loan_id}}/cancel",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "loans", "{{loan_id}}", "cancel"]
            },
            "description": "Cancels a PENDING_COLLATERAL loan. 204 on success. Fails if loan already ACTIVE or terminal."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "PATCH /v1/loans/:id/release-address",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"collateral_release_address\": \"jeremy@blink.sv\"\n}" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/loans/{{loan_id}}/release-address",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "loans", "{{loan_id}}", "release-address"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/loans/:id/add-collateral",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (body.topup_id) pm.collectionVariables.set('topup_id', body.topup_id);",
                  "  if (body.payment_request) pm.collectionVariables.set('topup_payment_request', body.payment_request);",
                  "  if (body.receiving_address) pm.collectionVariables.set('topup_payment_hash', body.receiving_address);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/loans/{{loan_id}}/add-collateral",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "loans", "{{loan_id}}", "add-collateral"]
            },
            "description": "**Customer-initiated collateral top-up on an ACTIVE loan.**\n\nReturns a fresh **variable-amount** Lightning invoice — the customer chooses how much SAT to send. 30-min expiry.\n\nResponse 201:\n```\n{\n  \"topup_id\":          \"uuid\",\n  \"loan_id\":           \"uuid\",\n  \"payment_request\":   \"lnbc...\",\n  \"receiving_address\": \"<payment hash>\",\n  \"expires_at\":        \"ISO-8601\"\n}\n```\n\nThe test script captures `topup_id` + `topup_payment_hash` into collection variables — use the latter as `payment_hash` in the next Blink webhook simulation to mark the top-up RECEIVED.\n\n**Errors:**\n- 404 Loan not found (or not yours)\n- 409 Loan not ACTIVE\n- 409 ADD_COLLATERAL_ALREADY_PENDING — only one open top-up per loan at a time"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/loans/:id/claim-inflow",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/loans/{{loan_id}}/claim-inflow",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "loans", "{{loan_id}}", "claim-inflow"]
            },
            "description": "**Customer claims an unmatched repayment inflow against this loan.**\n\nUse this when a customer has 2+ ACTIVE loans (PalmPay webhook can't auto-disambiguate) or when the auto-match path stored an unmatched Inflow for any reason.\n\nLooks up the most recent unmatched NGN Inflow for the authenticated user where:\n- `amount ≥ N10,000` (MIN_PARTIAL_REPAYMENT_NGN)\n- `created_at ≥ now − 24h`\n- `is_matched = false`, `source_type IS NULL`\n\nThen credits it via the same waterfall as auto-match (`match_method='CUSTOMER_CLAIM'`).\n\nResponse 200: same shape as `creditInflow` — `{ loan_id, new_status, applied_to_*, overpay_ngn, outstanding_ngn }`.\n\n**Errors:**\n- 404 Loan not found / not yours\n- 404 NO_UNMATCHED_INFLOW — nothing in the 24h window above floor\n- 409 Loan not ACTIVE"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "6. Webhooks (simulated)",
      "description": "Forge inbound provider webhooks with valid signatures for local testing.\n\n- Blink: Svix-signed HMAC-SHA256; pre-request script computes the signature from `blink_webhook_secret`.\n- PalmPay collection: omits the `sign` field — the provider's verifier returns true when absent. Same path is used by real PalmPay virtual account payments.\n- PalmPay payout: must include a valid `sign` (RSA-SHA1 with merchant private key). Forging is non-trivial; in production the real provider sends these.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/webhooks/blink  (collateral confirmed)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Build body from variables so accountId/walletId/paymentHash stay in sync.",
                  "const body = {",
                  "  accountId: pm.collectionVariables.get('blink_account_id'),",
                  "  eventType: 'receive.lightning',",
                  "  walletId:  pm.collectionVariables.get('blink_wallet_btc_id'),",
                  "  transaction: {",
                  "    initiationVia: {",
                  "      type:        'Lightning',",
                  "      paymentHash: pm.collectionVariables.get('payment_hash'),",
                  "    },",
                  "    status:             'SUCCESS',",
                  "    settlementAmount:   Number(pm.collectionVariables.get('blink_settlement_amount') || 21000),",
                  "    settlementCurrency: 'BTC',",
                  "    createdAt:          new Date().toISOString(),",
                  "  },",
                  "};",
                  "const raw = JSON.stringify(body);",
                  "pm.request.body.raw = raw;",
                  "",
                  "// Svix sign: HMAC-SHA256 of `{msg_id}.{timestamp}.{raw_body}` with base64-decoded secret.",
                  "const msg_id = 'msg_test_' + Date.now();",
                  "const ts     = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000).toString();",
                  "const signed = msg_id + '.' + ts + '.' + raw;",
                  "",
                  "const secret_b64 = pm.collectionVariables.get('blink_webhook_secret').replace(/^whsec_/, '');",
                  "const secret_bytes = CryptoJS.enc.Base64.parse(secret_b64);",
                  "const hmac = CryptoJS.HmacSHA256(signed, secret_bytes);",
                  "const sig = CryptoJS.enc.Base64.stringify(hmac);",
                  "",
                  "pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'svix-id',        value: msg_id });",
                  "pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'svix-timestamp', value: ts });",
                  "pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'svix-signature', value: 'v1,' + sig });",
                  "",
                  "// Remove Idempotency-Key — webhook endpoint is anonymous and dedups on provider_reference.",
                  "pm.request.headers.remove('Idempotency-Key');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/webhooks/blink", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "webhooks", "blink"] },
            "description": "**Simulates a Blink lightning receive.**\n\nPre-request script builds the body from collection variables (`blink_account_id`, `blink_wallet_btc_id`, `payment_hash`), computes a valid Svix HMAC-SHA256 signature, and sets the `svix-id` / `svix-timestamp` / `svix-signature` headers.\n\nSet `blink_settlement_amount` to override the default 21,000 sats.\n\nOn success: loan transitions PENDING_COLLATERAL → ACTIVE, a Disbursement is created, and an Outflow is dispatched via the active disbursement provider (PalmPay)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/webhooks/palmpay  (collection — repayment received)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.request.headers.remove('Idempotency-Key');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"orderNo\": \"pp_collection_test_0001\",\n  \"orderStatus\": 2,\n  \"createdTime\": 1713700000000,\n  \"updateTime\": 1713700000000,\n  \"currency\": \"NGN\",\n  \"orderAmount\": 5000000,\n  \"payerAccountNo\": \"0123456789\",\n  \"payerAccountName\": \"Jeremy Ikwuje\",\n  \"payerBankName\": \"GTBank\",\n  \"virtualAccountNo\": \"{{virtual_account_no}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/webhooks/palmpay", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "webhooks", "palmpay"] },
            "description": "**Simulates a PalmPay virtual-account inbound transfer (repayment).**\n\n- `orderAmount` is in **cents** — 5000000 = ₦50,000.00 (a partial repayment, well above the ₦10,000 floor).\n- `orderStatus`: 2 = SUCCESS (PALMPAY_ORDER_STATUS_SUCCESS). The handler skips anything else.\n- `virtualAccountNo` must match a `user_repayment_accounts.virtual_account_no` row. Set the `virtual_account_no` collection var first (auto-populated when KYC tier-1 succeeds in your local env, or set it manually from the DB).\n\n**v1.1 matching flow** (no `accountReference`, no narration):\n1. Resolve user from `virtualAccountNo` → no match → unmatched (`no_user_for_va`), ops paged.\n2. Floor check: amount < ₦10,000 → unmatched (`below_floor`), ops paged.\n3. Find user's ACTIVE loans. Zero → unmatched. Multiple → unmatched (use claim-inflow endpoint).\n4. Exactly one → auto-credit via the waterfall (custody → interest → principal → overpay).\n\n`sign` is deliberately omitted — the verifier returns true when absent (collection path only).\n\nResponse: plain-text `\"success\"` (PalmPay's required ack format)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/webhooks/palmpay  (payout — disbursement status)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.request.headers.remove('Idempotency-Key');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"orderId\": \"DISBURSEMENT_ID:outflow:1\",\n  \"orderNo\": \"palmpay_txn_abc123\",\n  \"appId\": \"L250919160477027524951\",\n  \"currency\": \"NGN\",\n  \"amount\": 300000,\n  \"orderStatus\": 2,\n  \"sessionId\": \"sess_xyz\",\n  \"completeTime\": 1713700000000,\n  \"sign\": \"REPLACE_WITH_REAL_RSA_SIGNATURE\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/webhooks/palmpay", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["v1", "webhooks", "palmpay"] },
            "description": "**Simulates a PalmPay payout status update.**\n\n`orderId` matches the regex `/:outflow:\\d+$/` so the controller routes it to the payout branch (not collection).\n\n- `orderStatus`: 1 = processing, 2 = success, 3 = failed\n- `sign` must be a valid RSA-SHA1 signature over MD5-of-sorted-params using the merchant private key. Forging requires the `PALMPAY_PRIVATE_KEY` from `.env`.\n\nNote: even on webhook receipt, the handler **re-queries PalmPay** to independently confirm the status before mutating outflow state — so a forged webhook alone cannot flip a payout to successful against a real PalmPay endpoint."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
